ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend this course. It provided a very thorough introduction into diagnostic measures and techniques.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course was very helpful for understanding how the procedures for making diagnostic decisions are carried out in clinical settings, which is pertinent to my research. It was especially helpful when Dr. O'Brien reviewed how the new DSM has changed from the previous version throughout the course. It provided a fresh perspective of where the field of clinical psychology is moving towards and how the field recognizes its weaknesses and implement changes to strengthen them.
Becoming familiar with diagnostic requirements for disorders will likely be very relevant to my research, as this has helped to frame the issues I wish to study.
